## 15. StateFlow & SharedFlow

### 15.1 StateFlow — Latest-Value Holder

`StateFlow` is a hot flow that always holds the **latest value** and emits it to new collectors immediately.

```kotlin
import kotlinx.coroutines.flow.*
import kotlinx.coroutines.*

class CounterViewModel : ViewModel() {

    // MutableStateFlow has an initial value
    private val _count = MutableStateFlow(0)
    val count: StateFlow<Int> = _count.asStateFlow() // Read-only exposure

    fun increment() {
        _count.value++
        // or: _count.update { it + 1 } (thread-safe)
    }

    fun decrement() {
        _count.update { currentValue -> maxOf(0, currentValue - 1) }
    }

    fun reset() {
        _count.value = 0
    }
}

// In Fragment:
viewLifecycleOwner.lifecycleScope.launch {
    viewLifecycleOwner.repeatOnLifecycle(Lifecycle.State.STARTED) {
        viewModel.count.collect { count ->
            binding.countTextView.text = count.toString()
        }
    }
}
```

### 15.2 SharedFlow — Multi-Subscriber Events

`SharedFlow` is a hot flow for **one-time events** (snackbar, navigation, dialog).

```kotlin
import kotlinx.coroutines.flow.*
import kotlinx.coroutines.*

class LoginViewModel : ViewModel() {

    // SharedFlow for one-time events (no initial value, no replay by default)
    private val _events = MutableSharedFlow<LoginEvent>()
    val events: SharedFlow<LoginEvent> = _events.asSharedFlow()

    fun login(email: String, password: String) {
        viewModelScope.launch {
            try {
                val user = withContext(Dispatchers.IO) {
                    authRepository.login(email, password)
                }
                _events.emit(LoginEvent.Success(user))
            } catch (e: InvalidCredentialsException) {
                _events.emit(LoginEvent.InvalidCredentials)
            } catch (e: Exception) {
                _events.emit(LoginEvent.Error(e.message ?: "Login failed"))
            }
        }
    }
}

sealed class LoginEvent {
    data class Success(val user: User) : LoginEvent()
    object InvalidCredentials : LoginEvent()
    data class Error(val message: String) : LoginEvent()
}

// In Activity:
viewLifecycleOwner.lifecycleScope.launch {
    viewLifecycleOwner.repeatOnLifecycle(Lifecycle.State.STARTED) {
        viewModel.events.collect { event ->
            when (event) {
                is LoginEvent.Success            -> navigateToHome(event.user)
                is LoginEvent.InvalidCredentials -> showSnackbar("Invalid email or password")
                is LoginEvent.Error              -> showSnackbar(event.message)
            }
        }
    }
}
```

### StateFlow vs SharedFlow Comparison

| Feature | StateFlow | SharedFlow |
|---|---|---|
| Initial value | Required | Not required |
| Replay count | 1 (latest) | Configurable (0–N) |
| Default use case | UI state | One-time events |
| New subscriber gets | Latest value immediately | Nothing (unless replay > 0) |
| Duplicate values | Skipped (distinct until changed) | All values emitted |
| Thread-safe | Yes | Yes |

