## 21. withContext — Thread Switching

`withContext` is the primary way to **switch threads** in Android development.

```kotlin
import kotlinx.coroutines.*

class ImageProcessor {

    // Orchestration runs on Main, switches threads as needed
    suspend fun processAndDisplayImage(uri: Uri): Bitmap = withContext(Dispatchers.Main) {

        // Step 1: Load from disk (IO)
        val rawBitmap: Bitmap = withContext(Dispatchers.IO) {
            BitmapFactory.decodeStream(contentResolver.openInputStream(uri))
        }

        // Step 2: Apply filters (CPU intensive)
        val processedBitmap: Bitmap = withContext(Dispatchers.Default) {
            applyFilters(rawBitmap)
        }

        // Step 3: Update UI (back on Main — automatic after withContext)
        imageView.setImageBitmap(processedBitmap)
        processedBitmap
    }

    private fun applyFilters(bitmap: Bitmap): Bitmap {
        // Heavy image processing...
        return bitmap
    }
}
```

### withContext vs launch for Thread Switching

```kotlin
// withContext — returns a result, sequential
val result: String = withContext(Dispatchers.IO) {
    fetchFromNetwork() // Must finish before moving on
}
println(result)

// launch — fire and forget, does NOT return a value
launch(Dispatchers.IO) {
    saveToDatabase() // Runs concurrently
}
println("Database save started in background")
