## 28. Performance Best Practices

### 1. Use `stateIn` for Expensive Flows

```kotlin
// Without stateIn — subscribes to DB every time UI rotates
val users: Flow<List<User>> = repository.getUsersFlow()

// ✅ With stateIn — single subscription, survives rotation
val users: StateFlow<List<User>> = repository.getUsersFlow()
    .stateIn(
        scope = viewModelScope,
        started = SharingStarted.WhileSubscribed(5000L), // keeps active 5s after last subscriber
        initialValue = emptyList()
    )
```

### 2. Use `debounce` for Search / Input

```kotlin
class SearchViewModel : ViewModel() {

    private val _query = MutableStateFlow("")

    val searchResults: StateFlow<List<Product>> = _query
        .debounce(500L)           // Wait 500ms after last keystroke
        .filter { it.length > 2 } // Only search for 3+ chars
        .distinctUntilChanged()   // Don't search same query twice
        .flatMapLatest { query -> // Cancel previous search if new query comes
            repository.search(query)
        }
        .stateIn(viewModelScope, SharingStarted.Lazily, emptyList())

    fun onQueryChanged(query: String) {
        _query.value = query
    }
}
```

### 3. `flowOn` to Offload Flow to Background Thread

```kotlin
// ✅ Use flowOn to run upstream flow on IO thread
fun getExpensiveData(): Flow<List<Data>> = flow {
    val data = database.loadAll() // Heavy DB query
    emit(data)
}
.map { list -> list.filter { it.isActive } } // Also on IO
.flowOn(Dispatchers.IO) // Everything above this runs on IO
// Collectors always get items on their original dispatcher
```

### 4. `conflate()` to Skip Stale Values

```kotlin
// If processor is slower than producer, skip old values
fastProducingFlow
    .conflate()  // Drop intermediate values, always process latest
    .collect { value ->
        delay(500) // Slow processing
        render(value) // Only latest value is rendered
    }
```

### 5. Use `distinctUntilChanged()`

```kotlin
// Don't re-render if value hasn't changed
viewModel.userName
    .distinctUntilChanged() // Skip duplicate emissions
    .collect { name -> binding.nameText.text = name }
```

